Place pork and onion in 3 1/2 to 4-quart slow cooker; add 1/2 cup of the barbecue sauce. Cover and cook on Low setting 9 to 10 hours or until pork shreds easily. While still in slow cooker, shred pork with 2 forks. Stir in preserves and remaining 1/4 cup barbecue sauce. Season to taste with salt and pepper, if desired. Serve shredded pork on buns.